  <answer><![CDATA[<div class="c-page-content">
<p>Set 1,000 kilometers away from mainland Portugal, walking holidays to <a data-udi="umb://document/79d3f06e8ff24a2aa77c6ed3d71d05bb" href="/{localLink:umb://document/79d3f06e8ff24a2aa77c6ed3d71d05bb}" title="Madeira" data-anchor="#">Madeira</a> offer a real sense of adventure. Some hikes are easy meanders between orchards and prehistoric laurel forests; others clamber up (and up and up) to mountains and gorges. What sets Madeira apart is its year-round subtropical climate, making it an absolute haven for walkers and nature lovers alike.</p>
</div>]]></answer>
